# Google Calendar API Configuration (Direct OAuth)
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret_here

# Instructions for Google Sign-In Setup:
# 1. Go to https://console.developers.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select an existing one
# 3. Enable the Google Calendar API
# 4. Go to "Credentials" and create "OAuth 2.0 Client ID"
# 5. Set Application type to "Web application"
# 6. Add Authorized JavaScript origins:
#    - http://localhost:5173 (for development)
#    - https://your-domain.com (for production)
# 7. Add Authorized redirect URIs:
#    - http://localhost:5173/auth/callback (for development)
#    - https://your-domain.com/auth/callback (for production)
# 8. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret to your .env file
# 9. Create a .env file in your project root and add:
#    VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_actual_client_id_here
#    VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_actual_client_secret_here

# Note: The VITE_ prefix is required for Vite to expose these variables to the frontend